    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove savings limit on Universal Credit for employees ineligible for JSS",
        "additional_details": "The new Job Support Scheme (JSS) doesn\u2019t offer financial support when there are no available work hours. Currently people are ineligible if they hold a certain amount of savings but a temporary change of eligibility would avoid the need to use hard earned future savings and investments during the downturn.",
        "background": "Change access criteria to universal credit for people that remain employed in industries crippled by Covid-19 (e.g. arts, travel, tourism and aviation)",
